    {
      "id": "fff1591e5fb68ffd1d28292c30e43c9ebe82ccf9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 19:14:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(3 inline comments)\n\nPatch looks functionally correct.  However, I'm always reluctant to add dedicated hash implementations instead of using cfs_hash, since it is designed for scalability and SMP locking already.\n\nIt looks like this hash is protected by the_lnet_lock, but in the future we might want to make that more fine grained also.\n\nI see that cfs_hash already has a CFS_HASH_NO_LOCK mode, where the caller is doing all of the locking, so I would be happy if this was converted over to cfs_hash, but I also am (reluctantly) OK with the current implementation.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
